Wash and dry all produce.

Quarter @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Core, deseed, and
finely dice @poblano pepper{1}. Dice @roma tomato{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} with a squeeze of lime
juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add onion and poblano; cook, stirring occasionally, until
browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, diced tomato, and
@tomato paste{1.5%ounce} until combined; cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir @black beans{13.4%ounce} and their liquid, @Tex-Mex paste{1},
@veggie stock concentrate{1}, and @water{1/2%cup} into pot with veggies.

> Use 1 cup water for 4 servings.

Bring to a simmer, uncovered, then reduce heat to medium low. Cook, stirring
often, until flavors meld and soup is slightly thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Taste
and season with salt and pepper.

> Add a splash more water if the soup ends up thicker than you like.

Meanwhile, pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems.

Divide soup between #bowls{} and dollop with lime sour cream. Sprinkle with
@Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and cilantro leaves. Serve with
@blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} for dipping and any remaining lime wedges
on the side.